# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# YouTube Automation Pipeline — environment configuration
# Copy this file to `.env` (same folder) and fill in your real values.
# `.env` is gitignored — never commit real keys.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Anthropic (script/spec/channel/analysis generation) ──
# Required for: script gen, board-spec gen, channel gen, analytics:analyze.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# ── Fish Audio S1 — default TTS backend (Issue B) ──
# Get a key at https://fish.audio (paid/hosted API). When set, `npm run voiceover`
# uses Fish S1 by default. When ABSENT, the pipeline falls back to the Windows
# SAPI stand-in with a clear message. Per-channel voice id lives in the channel's
# channel.spec.json -> audioIdentity.voice (a Fish reference_id).
FISH_API_KEY=fa-...
# Optional: override the default TTS backend (fish | sapi). Default: fish.
# TTS_BACKEND=fish

# ── Transcription (word timestamps) — pluggable backend ──
# The user chooses a backend at setup. local = Python `openai-whisper` (free/offline, needs
# Python+torch). cloud = any OpenAI-compatible /audio/transcriptions endpoint with word-level
# timestamps (zero install). auto = local if installed, else cloud. Default: auto.
# TRANSCRIBE_BACKEND=auto
# Cloud key (falls back to GROQ_API_KEY, then OPENAI_API_KEY). Groq's whisper-large-v3 is fast/cheap.
# TRANSCRIBE_API_KEY=gsk_...
# Optional cloud overrides. Defaults: Groq endpoint + whisper-large-v3.
# TRANSCRIBE_API_URL=https://api.groq.com/openai/v1/audio/transcriptions
# TRANSCRIBE_MODEL=whisper-large-v3
# (Note: DeepFilterNet denoise was removed — clean/AI voiceover needs no denoise step.)

# ── YouTube Data API v3 + Analytics API (Parts 1 & 2) ──
# Create an OAuth 2.0 "Desktop app" client in Google Cloud Console, enable the
# "YouTube Data API v3" and "YouTube Analytics API", then paste the client id/secret.
# Run `npm run youtube:auth <channel>` ONCE per channel to mint a refresh token
# (saved to channels/<id>/youtube.auth.json, gitignored).
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=...apps.googleusercontent.com
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=...
# Loopback port used during the one-time OAuth handshake (must match an authorized
# redirect URI on the client, e.g. http://localhost:4180/oauth2callback). Default: 4180.
# OAUTH_REDIRECT_PORT=4180

# ── Outlier research (session 7) — data-driven topic selection ──
# A simple YouTube Data API key (NOT OAuth) for public niche search: the packaging engine finds
# videos that beat their channel's subscriber baseline and conditions topics on proven demand.
# Create at console.cloud.google.com → APIs & Services → Credentials → API key (restrict to
# "YouTube Data API v3"). Absent ⇒ research self-skips (topics stay taste-based). `npm run
# research <channel>` previews the signal.
YOUTUBE_API_KEY=...

# ── Quota (Part 1) ──
# YouTube Data API default daily quota is 10,000 units; an upload costs ~1,600.
# The pipeline tracks an approximate daily tally and refuses uploads that would
# exceed this ceiling. Raise/lower if your project has a different quota.
# YT_DAILY_QUOTA=10000
